message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The only vaccination that matches the description provided is Pneumovax, which is a pneumococcal polysaccharide vaccine used to prevent pneumococcal disease in children and adults. Hib vaccine is a conjugate vaccine used to prevent Haemophilus influenzae type b infections, Live attenuated influenza vaccine is a live virus vaccine used to prevent influenza, and Menactra is a conjugate vaccine used to prevent meningococcal disease.
